'''Rokrul''' was a [[City/Legends|village]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Nelvaan/Legends|Nelvaan]] in the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]]' [[Nelvaan system/Legends|Koobi system]]. It was built within an indentation on the side of a cliff and was populated by the local [[Nelvaanian/Legends|Nelvaanians]]. The villagers of Rokrul learned that the scales from the tail of the local [[Horax/Legends|horax]] could be used to create an [[Horax scale elixir/Legends|elixir]] that would repel the large beasts, and bringing back a scale from one of the animals became a rite of passage for young Nelvaanian [[Gender/Legends|boys]], earning them a place in the [[Soldier/Legends|warrior]] ranks.

During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], the [[Techno Union/Legends|Techno Union]] captured all the adult men from the village and began experiments on them in hopes of creating a super-Nelvaanian [[Army/Legends|army]]. In [[19 BBY]], [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] landed on the planet and came in contact with the remaining villagers, who informed the two of their plight. Skywalker was then revealed to be the answer to a prophecy stating that the [[Holt Kazed]], or "Ghost Hand," would free the captive men due to his [[Cybernetics/Legends|prosthetic hand]]. Skywalker located and destroyed the [[Techno Union laboratory|Techno Union base]], freeing all the Nelvaanian men who survived the [[Battle of Nelvaan|battle]]. The Jedi Knight returned to the village with the men and reunited them with their families.

==Description==
===A cliffside village===
[[File:Nelvaanians.jpg|thumb|left|300px|The women and children Nelvaanians of Rokrul village]]
Rokrul was a small [[City/Legends|village]] on the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Nelvaan/Legends|Nelvaan]], in the [[Nelvaan system/Legends|Koobi system]].<ref name="CSWEKoobi">{{CSWECite|II|224|Koobi system}}</ref> The village's buildings were carved out of the rock within an indentation on the side of a cliff. The structures were mostly giant, hollowed-out mounds protruding from the floor.<ref name="CW23" /> The village was populated by at least 116 [[Nelvaanian/Legends|Nelvaanians]]<ref name="Note1" /> belonging to several tribes, and the village was a result of a loose affiliation among the tribes created for protection and assistance.<ref name="CSWERokful" />

===Culture===
{{Quote|They're summoning the spirit of the fire. The mother weeps, she is sick. Our warriors have failed. Failed to heal the mother. Into the never-ending winter, a stranger comes. But tell us why he has come. What is his purpose?"<br />"Holt Kazed."<br />"They're saying 'Ghost Hand.'|Obi-Wan Kenobi translates the Holt Kazed prophesy told by Orvos|<ref name="CW23" />}}
The culture of the village necessitated that the strongest [[Gender/Legends|men]] be [[Soldier/Legends|warriors]] and [[Scout/Legends|scouts]], responsible for [[Hunting/Legends|hunting]] and protection, while the women stay in the village and do the building, gathering, and&mdash;most important of all&mdash;raising of the [[Youngling/Legends|children]], as [[Parent/Legends|motherhood]] was sacred in Nelvaanian tradition. The villagers regarded their [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] as the "[[Great Mother]]," and whenever something tragic happened in nature, they felt as if the Great Mother had been hurt. The villagers also believed in a prophecy that stated the [[Holt Kazed]], or "Ghost Hand," would come to save the Nelvaanians from a crisis sometime in the future.<ref name="DB1">{{DB|species|nelvaanian|Nelvaanian}}</ref> Children were considered precious treasures, regardless of gender, and the elders were paid great respect.<ref name="NEGAS">''[[The New Essential Guide to Alien Species]]''</ref>

[[File:Tuzes-Adaz-and-Orvos.png|thumb|right|300px|Chieftain Tuzes-Adaz and shaman Orvos of Rokrul]]
The [[Chief/Legends|chief]] of a tribe was often one of the tribe's eldest members who assumed the position after a long, productive life. They were assisted in their ruling by their bond-mate and were advised by the [[Shaman/Legends|shaman]] of the tribe. As all members of a tribe shared communal duties, with every member participating in the rituals for their gender, there was no special test that an elder had to pass in order to become chief. Rather, chiefs were selected by the "Great Mother" due to a showing of respect and deference on the elder's part. The decision was not questioned by any of the villagers.<ref name="NEGAS" />

Village [[Clothing/Legends|clothing]] was different for men, women, and children. Women wore long [[Color/Legends|brown]], gray, and red gowns, while the men wore pants and loin cloths with no top. Children wore [[Robe/Legends|robe]]-like garments that were often brown in color.<ref name="CW23" /> During celebrations, the villagers also wore giant masks and [[Gauntlet/Legends|gauntlets]] while dancing around a [[Fire/Legends|bonfire]].<ref name="CW25">{{CW|25}}</ref> These fires were occasionally used to speak to the "[[Spirit of the Fire]]," a spiritual figure in Nelvaanian tradition.<ref name="CW23" />

==History==
===The horax elixir===
{{Quote|It seems you've interrupted the boy's rite of passage, or test.|Kenobi, to Skywalker|<ref name="CW23" />}}
[[File:Interrupted-horax-hunt.png|thumb|left|300px|Bringing back a scale from the tail of a horax became a rite of passage for young Nelvaanian boys.]]
The villagers of Rokrul discovered that an [[Horax scale elixir/Legends|elixir]] used to repel the vicious [[Horax/Legends|horax]] beasts in the area could be made using the tail scales from one of the creatures. One scale could be used to make a perimeter around the village that would last for an entire [[Standard year/Legends|year]]. It eventually became a rite of passage for young Nelvaanian boys to venture out at the start of the year and bring back a scale from the tail of a horax, earning them a place among the male warrior ranks if successful.<ref name="HoraxDB">{{DB|creature|horax|horax}}</ref>

===Liberation from the Techno Union===
{{Quote|You've done a great thing for these people. Well done, Anakin.|Kenobi, to Skywalker|<ref name="CW25" />}}
During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]],<ref name="CW23" /> a [[The galaxy/Legends|galaxy]]-spanning conflict between the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]] that lasted from [[19 BBY]] to [[22 BBY]], the Confederate-allied<ref name="TNEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> [[Techno Union/Legends|Techno Union]] created a [[Techno Union laboratory|laboratory]] on Nelvaan. The Techno Union base functioned off a [[siphon generator]] that drained thermal energy from the surrounding area, plunging the nearby village Rokrul into an endless [[Winter/Legends|winter]].<ref name="DB2">{{DB|location|nelvaan|Nelvaan}}</ref> Although the village's shaman, [[Orvos]], had predicted a coming [[Water/Legends|ice]] age, the intensity and abruptness of the cold took the village by surprise. The villagers, not knowing what caused the winter, believed that the "Great Mother" was ill and that she had to be healed in order for the warm weather to return.<ref name="DB1" /> To discover what caused the Great Mother's [[Disease/Legends|illness]], the village sent out its male scouts and warriors. All of the men, including a warrior named [[Harvos]],<ref name="CSWEHarvos">{{CSWECite|II|24|Harvos}}</ref> were captured by the Techno Union and mutated into [[Cyborg/Legends|cyborgs]] for the war effort.<ref name="DB2" />

[[File:Rokrul_celebration.png|thumb|right|300px|The villagers celebrate the return of their men.]]
In 19 BBY, [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]]<ref name="TNEC" /> [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and<ref name="CW23" /> [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]]<ref name="TNEC" /> [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] landed on the planet and were taken to the village after interfering with the initiation process of a [[Tuzes-Adaz's son|young Nelvaanian boy]], the son of<ref name="CW23" /> Chieftain [[Tuzes-Adaz]].<ref name="CSWEAdaz" /> Upon the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi's]] arrival at the village, Tuzes-Adaz told Kenobi and Skywalker of the legendary Holt Kazed, or "Ghost Hand," and why all the men of the community had vanished. Orvos, the local shaman, covered Skywalker's body with [[bruise-leech crawler]]s during a ritualistic practice. Afterward, Kenobi stated that this would be Skywalker's final [[Jedi Trials/Legends|Jedi Trial]], the Trial of Spirit, and the villagers sent Skywalker to rescue the Nelvaanian men.<ref name="CW23" /> After Skywalker infiltrated and successfully [[Battle of Nelvaan|destroyed]] the Techno Union base,<ref name="CW25" /> consequentially returning warmth to Rokrul,<ref name="CSWERokful" /> he<ref name="TNEC" /> led the mutated men back to the village. After some initial hesitation, the women and children learned to accept them once again, throwing a celebration around a large bonfire.<ref name="CW25" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|&hellip;is a little reference to the Canadian studio that did all those wonderful ''Star Wars'' cartoons back in&hellip;back when we were kids. And ''Rock & Rule'', fantastic film by Nelvana studios, so we use the dog-headed peoples that they were so fond of using as the natives here.|[[Paul Rudish]] explains the inspiration for several aspects of the village|<ref name="Commentary">[[Star Wars: Clone Wars Volume Two|''Star Wars: Clone Wars'' Volume Two]] commentary</ref>}}
[[File:Nelvana.svg|thumb|left|270px|Nelvana's logo]]
Rokrul first appeared in the [[Chapter 23 (Star Wars: Clone Wars)|twenty-third chapter]]<ref name="CW23" /> of the [[2003]] animated series ''[[Star Wars: Clone Wars]]'', which aired on [[March 23]], [[2005]].<ref name="TV.com">{{TVcom|url=shows/star-wars-clone-wars/chapter-xxiii-370295|text=Star Wars: Clone Wars - Season 2, Episode 3: Chapter XXIII}}</ref> The village was first named in the [[StarWars.com]] [[Databank (original)|Databank]] entry for Nelvaan.<ref name="DB2" /> Rokrul's name is similar in pronunciation to the title of [[Wikipedia:Rock & Rule|''Rock & Rule'']], an animated film by [[Wikipedia:Canada|Canadian]] animation studio [[Nelvana]]. The film was an influence on the character design of the Nelvaanians. Influences on the culture of the village included ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]'', the fantasy film [[Wikipedia:The Dark Crystal|''The Dark Crystal'']], and [[Wikipedia:Native Americans in the United States|Native American]] mythos.<ref name="Commentary" />

